        </dd>

        
                  <dt>Publication History</dt>
          <dd>
                                        <p>
                                              <em>Catalogue of the Drawings of Landscapes and Trees by Fra Bartolommeo</em>, auct. cat., Sotheby's (London, England, November 20, 1957), lot 4, p. vii; repr. no. 4, pp. 9-10
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              <em>Exhibition of Old Master Drawings</em>, exh. cat., P. & D. Colnaghi & Co. Ltd. (London, England, June 17, 1958 - July 17, 1958), cat. no. 13, recto repr.
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Eunice Williams, <em>Master Drawings and Watercolors: The Hofer Collection</em>, exh. cat., ed. Konrad Oberhuber and William W. Robinson, Harvard University Art Museums (Cambridge, 1984), cat. no. 2, pp. 16-17, and p. 10; repr. p. 76, pl. 2 (recto and verso)
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Agnes Mongan, Konrad Oberhuber, and Jonathan Bober, <em>The Famous Italian Drawings at the Fogg Art Museum in Cambridge</em>, Silvana Editoriale (Milan, Italy, 1988), cat. no. 18, n.p., and pp. 13, 26 and 27, repr. color
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Chris Fischer, "Fra Bartolommeo's Landscape Drawings", <em>Mitteilungen des Kunsthistorischen Institutes in Florenz</em> (1989), 33. Bd., H. 2/3, pp. 301-342, pp. 325-326, 329-330, repr. p. 330 as no. 38
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Albert Jan Elen, <em>Italian Late-Medieval and Renaissance Drawing-Books from Giovannino de'Grassi to Palma Giovane: A Codicological Approach</em>, Privately Published (Leiden, 1995), under cat. no. 46, pp. 280 and 281
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Ernst-Gerhard Güse and Alexander Perrig, <em>Zeichnungen aus der Toskana: Das Zeitalter Michelangelos</em>, exh. cat., Saarland Museum and Prestel-Verlag (Saarbrücken and Munich/New York, 1997), p. 296 (n. 1 under note section for cat. no. 12)
                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Joachim Jacoby, ed., <em>Raffael bis Tizian: Italienische Zeichnungen aus dem Städel Museum</em>, exh. cat., Michael Imhof-Verlag (Petersberg, Hessen, 2014), p. 65, p. 66 n. 10
                             </p>
                                    </dd>
        
